    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Taenitis flabellivenia are attributed to its bioactive compounds, which include flavonoids, saponins, and volatile oils. The antioxidant property of this plant is attributed to the scavenging of free radicals by flavonoids, resulting in the protection of cells from oxidative damage. Additionally, the antimicrobial property of Taenitis flabellivenia is due to the presence of saponins, which disrupt microbial cell membranes, ultimately leading to their death. The anti-inflammatory property of this plant is associated with the inhibition of pro-inflammatory enzymes by volatile oils, thereby reducing inflammation. Furthermore, the hepatoprotective and antiviral properties of Taenitis flabellivenia are attributed to its ability to modulate the immune system and prevent viral replication, respectively, thereby protecting the liver and preventing the progression of viral infections.",
